{"id": "1494889009107828826", "channel_id": "1494889009107828826", "author_id": "1438876647024496681", "author_name": "gacha_ping", "content": "Hello,\n\nI was concerned that feedback from the Korean community might not be fully delivered here, so I used AI assistance to summarize and share the opinions that have been discussed so far.\n\nI truly love this game. However, at the moment, a large portion of posts in the Korean community are focused on concerns regarding the 12-level breakthrough system.\n\nI am sharing this feedback in the hope that it can be helpful, so please do not take it as excessive criticism, but rather as constructive input for improving the game’s operation.\n\nPersonally, I also find the current situation quite unfortunate. Nevertheless, I sincerely hope that this update can lead to a healthier outcome—one that benefits both the developers and the players.\n\nThank you.", "timestamp": "2026-04-18T02:35:13.466000+00:00", "thread_id": "1494889009107828826", "reactions": [{"emoji": "Pandia_love", "emoji_id": "1459078512303411261", "count": 11}]}
{"id": "1494889333897822378", "channel_id": "1494889009107828826", "author_id": "1438876647024496681", "author_name": "gacha_ping", "content": "Consolidated Feedback (Structured Summary):\n\nThe core issue originates from the introduction of the 12-level breakthrough system, which has significantly impacted both balance and player experience.\n\n1. Monetization (BM) Concerns\nPlayers generally understand and are willing to support monetization. However, the current approach feels overly burdensome and may lead to negative outcomes.\nThe 12-level breakthrough system makes progression feel less like a choice and more like a necessity, increasing pressure on in-game resources and raising concerns about design intent.\n\n2. Balance & Design Issues\nEarly and free characters were released with relatively low breakthrough value, while newer characters receive significantly stronger benefits from the same system.\nThis creates a large performance gap, making some characters feel “mandatory” while older ones feel neglected.\n\n3. Player Experience Impact\nBecause there was no clear baseline for future power scaling, players made investment decisions under misleading expectations.\nAs a result, many feel they wasted resources on suboptimal choices, especially when experimenting with different characters.", "timestamp": "2026-04-18T02:36:30.902000+00:00", "thread_id": "1494889009107828826"}
{"id": "1494889347906797658", "channel_id": "1494889009107828826", "author_id": "1438876647024496681", "author_name": "gacha_ping", "content": "4. Endgame Content Design\nEndgame content appears to be balanced around the assumption of high breakthrough levels.\nUnlike other games where high investment is optional, here it feels effectively required.\n\n5. Trust & Communication Issues (Critical)\nThe current update direction differs significantly from previously communicated expectations.\nShort notice announcements and drastic changes have led to a perception of abrupt, unilateral decisions.\nPlayer backlash is not simply overreaction, but rooted in these inconsistencies.\n\n6. Monetization vs. Quality Gap\nWhile monetization models seem to follow industry trends, players feel that the overall game quality does not yet meet those same standards.\n\n7. Apology & Communication Quality\nThe recent apology lacked detail and clarity.\nPlayers expect clear explanations of:\n\nwhat caused the issue,\nhow it will be fixed, and\nwhat measures will prevent recurrence.\n\nWithout this, it is difficult to rebuild trust.", "timestamp": "2026-04-18T02:36:34.242000+00:00", "thread_id": "1494889009107828826"}
